You're their protectors.

11
00:00:39,880 --> 00:00:41,900
You can speculate all you want,

12
00:00:41,920 --> 00:00:43,780
but I implore you to verify your claims

13
00:00:43,960 --> 00:00:45,140
before making accusations.

14
00:00:45,240 --> 00:00:46,140
If you have no proof,

15
00:00:46,160 --> 00:00:47,820
don't ask me to prove my innocence.

16
00:00:47,960 --> 00:00:49,260
When I show you the proof,

17
00:00:49,400 --> 00:00:51,380
will I have to
show you an arrest warrant?

18
00:00:52,120 --> 00:00:53,340
What are you hiding?

19
00:00:53,920 --> 00:00:55,060
What are you afraid of?

20
00:02:20,640 --> 00:02:24,840
[In the Name of Justice]

21
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:27,840
[Episode 30]

22
00:02:31,440 --> 00:02:31,820
Son,

23
00:02:32,040 --> 00:02:32,740
I have a question for you:

24
00:02:33,800 --> 00:02:34,700
if

25
00:02:34,960 --> 00:02:37,460
some close friends of yours

26
00:02:38,640 --> 00:02:41,020
sneaked into the teacher's office

27
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:44,140
and saw the exam paper,

28
00:02:45,480 --> 00:02:46,940
and though you didn't take part,

29
00:02:47,640 --> 00:02:48,300
they

30
00:02:49,040 --> 00:02:49,700
still

31
00:02:50,320 --> 00:02:51,260
tipped you off

32
00:02:51,920 --> 00:02:53,780
on some key questions

33
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:55,180
which helped you ace the test,

34
00:02:56,080 --> 00:02:57,900
would you tell the teacher

35
00:02:58,240 --> 00:02:59,220
after finding out what they've done?

36
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:01,020
Of course.

37
00:03:01,040 --> 00:03:02,220
I have to report it to the teacher.

38
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:04,580
But you got a high score
because of that.

39
00:03:05,240 --> 00:03:07,060
But I didn't look at
the exam paper myself,

40
00:03:07,160 --> 00:03:08,540
nor did I do anything wrong,

41
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:09,500
so I'd definitely
report it to the teacher.

42
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:13,740
Aren't you worried your friends

43
00:03:14,280 --> 00:03:15,700
will feel betrayed by you?

44
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:18,100
I'd be doing it for their own good.

45
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:19,460
Isn't that what you

46
00:03:19,480 --> 00:03:20,900
and Mom always teach me?

47
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:32,300
But everyone knows you're good friends,

48
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:33,900
including the teacher.

49
00:03:35,080 --> 00:03:36,100
Aren't you worried

50
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:38,540
the teacher might think
you were in on it together?

51
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:40,580
But if I don't report it,

52
00:03:40,960 --> 00:03:42,780
and the teacher finds out later,

53
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:44,500
wouldn't that be harder to clear up?

54
00:03:55,080 --> 00:03:57,140
I'm sure you're already aware that the

55
00:03:57,560 --> 00:03:59,100
Provincial Political and Legal Affairs
Commission sent a special task force.

56
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:03,300
But do you know why?

57
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:09,380
It's right here in this meeting room

58
00:04:09,640 --> 00:04:10,700
where we've had countless meetings

59
00:04:10,960 --> 00:04:13,220
about the Wan Hai case

60
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:14,300
over the past three years.

61
00:04:14,840 --> 00:04:15,700
The verdict just came out,

62
00:04:17,080 --> 00:04:18,020
and the provincial office has already
raised questions.

63
00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:22,140
First, they cleared
the Zhang Wenjing Case,

64
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:24,980
then they found new problems
in the Wan Hai Case.

65
00:04:26,320 --> 00:04:27,700
At every meeting,

66
00:04:28,480 --> 00:04:29,660
you said everything was fine.

67
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:30,500
So why are we

68
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:32,260
facing such serious problems now?

69
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:34,260
Are there more problems coming?

70
00:04:34,280 --> 00:04:35,540
What else can go wrong?

71
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:37,900
Can anyone here tell me?

72
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:44,980
Upon notice
from the Provincial Committee,

73
00:04:45,680 --> 00:04:47,660
I've already briefed Mr. Jianing.

74
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:49,860
Some of you may face investigation

75
00:04:49,920 --> 00:04:52,540
and interviews by the task force.

76
00:04:52,680 --> 00:04:54,340
I hope everyone

77
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:55,900
can stay alert

78
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:57,260
and open-minded,

79
00:04:57,840 --> 00:04:59,420
while ensuring proper coordination

80
00:04:59,640 --> 00:05:01,660
within their own departments.

81
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:05,340
How long have Sun Fei and
Jiang Hongjun been in custody?

82
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:08,460
Ms. Lan, it's been three days.

83
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:10,660
The director of the Political Department

84
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:11,820
of Dongping Judicial Bureau

85
00:05:12,120 --> 00:05:13,820
will temporarily oversee the sub-bureau.

86
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:15,340
Three days?

87
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:17,700
Then they must have concrete evidence.

88
00:05:23,080 --> 00:05:25,060
As the lead official
in charge of the investigation,

89
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:26,500
you need to personally

90
00:05:27,480 --> 00:05:29,020
review the case files carefully

91
00:05:29,640 --> 00:05:31,900
identify all potential issues,

92
00:05:32,640 --> 00:05:33,180
and hand them to me.

93
00:05:33,840 --> 00:05:34,180
Yes, ma'am.

94
00:05:34,760 --> 00:05:35,420
And I want it fast.

95
00:05:35,920 --> 00:05:36,700
Yes, I understand.

96
00:05:37,280 --> 00:05:38,460
Same for you two's departments.

97
00:05:39,520 --> 00:05:41,060
The directors must go through
the case files personally

98
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:43,180
and report the potential issues
back to me.

99
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:44,780
We will investigate internally

100
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:46,980
and aim to uncover any faults ourselves.

101
00:05:47,320 --> 00:05:49,580
Taking initiative
is the best way to cooperate.

102
00:05:50,400 --> 00:05:51,620
We'll keep each other updated

103
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:53,500
around the clock these days.

104
00:05:54,360 --> 00:05:56,380
My phone will be on 24/7.

105
00:05:57,680 --> 00:05:59,020
Lastly, I want to say,

106
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:03,780
I sincerely hope that no one
is found at fault,

107
00:06:07,440 --> 00:06:08,540
and that all of you

108
00:06:10,840 --> 00:06:11,500
will stay out of trouble.

109
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:28,420
Everyone,

110
00:06:29,320 --> 00:06:30,420
there are a lot of case files to review,

111
00:06:30,840 --> 00:06:31,700
and we're short on time,

112
00:06:31,960 --> 00:06:32,540
so get started.

113
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:50,700
Based on the evidence we currently have,

114
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:53,940
the two key charges against Wan Hai-

115
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:55,940
forced deal and assault-

116
00:06:56,120 --> 00:06:56,740
have both been overturned.

117
00:06:57,640 --> 00:06:58,580
The Wan Hai case is largely

118
00:06:59,160 --> 00:07:01,420
confirmed as a miscarriage of justice.

119
00:07:02,120 --> 00:07:03,380
The Wanchuan Mining Accident

120
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:06,060
is a subsequent incident
of the Wan Hai case

121
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:06,860
and is still under investigation.

122
00:07:07,280 --> 00:07:07,700
Check this out.

123
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:11,420
Have some water.

124
00:07:11,440 --> 00:07:11,940
Thank you.

125
00:07:12,400 --> 00:07:12,780
Have some wate.

126
00:07:17,440 --> 00:07:19,060
We need to interview

127
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:20,140
and question

128
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:21,540
relevant officials

129
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:23,700
from various departments

130
00:07:24,080 --> 00:07:25,900
involved in the Wan Hai Case.

131
00:07:27,120 --> 00:07:28,060
Xu Yanwu from the police department.

132
00:07:28,880 --> 00:07:29,660
Wen Qin from the Court.

133
00:07:30,520 --> 00:07:31,980
Li Renjun from the Procuratorate.

134
00:07:32,960 --> 00:07:33,860
Any duty-related crimes

135
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:36,300
will be thoroughly investigated.

136
00:08:10,920 --> 00:08:11,820
Why are you still up?

137
00:08:23,080 --> 00:08:23,820
I was notified

138
00:08:27,640 --> 00:08:28,940
by the task force today

139
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:31,380
that I have to go in
for questioning tomorrow.

140
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:33,860
Task Force?

141
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:36,700
The Task Force
for Wanchuan Mining Accident,

142
00:08:38,040 --> 00:08:39,100
supervised by the
Provincial Anti-Crime Office,

143
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:41,060
coordinated by

144
00:08:41,920 --> 00:08:42,620
the Provincial Procuratorate,

145
00:08:43,280 --> 00:08:44,340
with support from the
Provincial High People's Court

146
00:08:45,320 --> 00:08:46,300
and Provincial Public Security Bureau.

147
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:48,060
Why do they want to see you?

148
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:49,980
To talk about the Wan Hai Case,

149
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:52,660
the mining accident,

150
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:56,820
Qiao Zhenxing's death,

151
00:08:58,160 --> 00:09:00,020
and who is the real mastermind
behind Dongping's organized crimes,

152
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:01,700
and who is

153
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:03,340
protecting them.

154
00:09:20,880 --> 00:09:21,340
Honey,

155
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:25,220
tell me honestly,

156
00:09:27,120 --> 00:09:28,060
are your recent dealings

157
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:30,380
with Chen Shenglong

158
00:09:32,760 --> 00:09:33,700
and the Tianlong Company

159
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:36,740
all legitimate business?

160
00:09:37,760 --> 00:09:39,820
We've already filed for eminent domain

161
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:41,740
over Hongjia Village

162
00:09:42,320 --> 00:09:43,940
because we plan to build

163
00:09:44,240 --> 00:09:45,660
a battery plant there,

164
00:09:45,920 --> 00:09:47,620
so that's the only area I need.

165
00:09:47,880 --> 00:09:48,580
I won't do

166
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:49,260
partnerships.

167
00:09:49,520 --> 00:09:50,220
It's either buy it all or nothing.

168
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:52,140
Full ownership is the only way

169
00:09:52,640 --> 00:09:53,940
I can be fully devoted.

170
00:09:54,360 --> 00:09:55,260
Why do you think

171
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:56,740
I sold you the house in Dadu Xishan
at half price?

172
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:59,380
How do you think
you got the house worth millions?

173
00:09:59,760 --> 00:10:00,420
You want to back out?

174
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:02,260
Let me tell you-no way!

175
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:03,820
The Wans' mine

176
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:10,700
is a generous gift from me.

177
00:10:11,640 --> 00:10:13,140
Now that you're in a
political-business partnership,

178
00:10:13,160 --> 00:10:15,820
accepting this house
can give others leverage over you,

179
00:10:16,040 --> 00:10:17,820
it could even lead to
duty-related crimes.

180
00:10:31,320 --> 00:10:32,220
Answer me,

181
00:10:34,560 --> 00:10:37,060
are your business dealings legitimate?

182
00:10:41,680 --> 00:10:42,980
He's responsible
for the mining accident.

183
00:10:43,640 --> 00:10:45,540
I've basically become his protector.

184
00:10:59,240 --> 00:11:00,540
Long wanted to

185
00:11:00,560 --> 00:11:02,100
break into the new energy sector.

186
00:11:02,360 --> 00:11:04,380
Yun's connection

187
00:11:04,400 --> 00:11:05,460
really helped Zijian a lot.

188
00:11:05,640 --> 00:11:08,020
Yun got him Wanchuan Mining,

189
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:10,420
which ensured Long's first step
in the new energy sector.

190
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:11,580
Mr. Chen

191
00:11:12,320 --> 00:11:13,340
is practically family to me,

192
00:11:13,680 --> 00:11:14,860
and Zijian is like a brother to me.

193
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:16,900
Besides, we didn't buy the house,

194
00:11:17,120 --> 00:11:19,860
Long gave it to us
as an employee benefit.

195
00:11:20,640 --> 00:11:22,780
It's a clearance sale.

196
00:11:23,080 --> 00:11:24,300
Anyone would've paid the same prize.

197
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:26,740
Which company is involved now?

198
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:28,100
Tianlong Company.

199
00:11:49,920 --> 00:11:52,620
Do you have any dealings
with the Tianlong Company?

200
00:11:53,720 --> 00:11:55,220
Tianlong Company? Yeah!

201
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:58,140
Isn't Chen Zijian, the general counsel,

202
00:11:58,160 --> 00:12:00,700
your brother-in-law?

203
00:12:00,920 --> 00:12:02,140
There is no material evidence

204
00:12:02,160 --> 00:12:03,660
to corroborate these crucial parts,
only witness testimony!

205
00:12:03,880 --> 00:12:04,500
The chain of custody

206
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:06,300
in the Wan Hai case is intact,

207
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:07,340
and the prosecution remains sound.

208
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:10,780
When I checked Tianlong's tax records,

209
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:13,300
I heard Mr. Qiao had also been there.

210
00:12:13,760 --> 00:12:15,900
I will report that you replaced
the prosecutor on your own,

211
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:18,740
and I'll sue you for malfeasance!

212
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:20,700
My wife Liu Yi is the deputy director
of the Development Zone.

213
00:12:21,120 --> 00:12:24,020
She helped Chen Shenglong
acquire Wanchuan Mining,

214
00:12:24,400 --> 00:12:25,140
[Presiding Judge]
and I was in charge

215
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:27,340
of the Wan Hai Case,

216
00:12:27,800 --> 00:12:30,420
you don't think that makes me
seem like their protector?

217
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:34,260
Come...

218
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:38,820
come with me tomorrow.

219
00:12:41,240 --> 00:12:42,060
I can't.

220
00:12:43,800 --> 00:12:44,380
I can't go.

221
00:12:45,720 --> 00:12:47,220
I... I won't be able to explain it.

222
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:48,500
Renjun,

223
00:12:48,960 --> 00:12:50,260
please don't say anything.

224
00:12:50,560 --> 00:12:52,660
I'm trying very hard
to cut ties with them

225
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:56,180
and make things right.

226
00:12:57,440 --> 00:12:59,260
Please believe me.
I just need a little more time.

227
00:13:02,520 --> 00:13:03,020
Renjun,

228
00:13:05,320 --> 00:13:06,300
if they start investigating me,

229
00:13:06,560 --> 00:13:07,700
I'm finished.

230
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:10,020
What will happen to this family?

231
00:13:10,440 --> 00:13:11,420
What about our son?

232
00:13:11,560 --> 00:13:12,340
Qiqi's still young.

233
00:13:13,800 --> 00:13:14,940
He needs a family.

234
00:13:19,080 --> 00:13:19,620
Renjun.

235
00:14:13,800 --> 00:14:14,180
Mr. Li,

236
00:14:15,120 --> 00:14:15,820
it's been a while.

237
00:15:11,240 --> 00:15:11,900
Mr. Li, hello.

238
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:13,500
We are the with the special Tack Force.

239
00:15:13,840 --> 00:15:14,580
We've asked you here

240
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:16,620
to clarify some details

241
00:15:16,920 --> 00:15:18,500
about the Wan Hai case.

242
00:15:18,800 --> 00:15:20,060
This conversation
is strictly confidential.

243
00:15:20,240 --> 00:15:20,900
Your cooperation is appreciated.

244
00:15:22,720 --> 00:15:23,180
Mr. Li,

245
00:15:25,240 --> 00:15:26,780
what's your view on the Wan Hai Case?

246
00:15:27,680 --> 00:15:28,820
Do you think

247
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:30,500
there has been any wrongdoing?

248
00:15:31,640 --> 00:15:32,420
No, I don't think so,

249
00:15:33,160 --> 00:15:34,540
otherwise, we wouldn't have
prosecuted it.

250
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:39,300
During Qiao Zhenxing's time
as lead prosecutor,

251
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:43,300
the case was twice sent back
for further police investigation.

252
00:15:44,160 --> 00:15:45,100
After you took over,

253
00:15:45,680 --> 00:15:47,100
did you verify the issues

254
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:48,300
he raised?

255
00:15:51,920 --> 00:15:52,660
During his handling of the case,

256
00:15:52,680 --> 00:15:54,180
we discussed it many times.

257
00:15:55,360 --> 00:15:56,100
I believe

258
00:15:56,600 --> 00:15:57,980
his approach was flawed.

259
00:15:58,120 --> 00:15:58,780
So you

260
00:15:59,800 --> 00:16:00,420
took him off the case?

261
00:16:09,480 --> 00:16:10,700
The Wan Hai Case has been going
for two years.

262
00:16:11,960 --> 00:16:12,700
Maybe you should

263
00:16:13,480 --> 00:16:14,140
take a break.

264
00:16:15,720 --> 00:16:16,500
Why was I taken off?

265
00:16:16,720 --> 00:16:18,380
Did I make mistakes or abuse my power?

266
00:16:20,360 --> 00:16:22,100
It was decided
by the Party Leadership Group.

267
00:16:23,840 --> 00:16:24,860
Who chaired
the Party Leadership Group meeting?

268
00:16:26,360 --> 00:16:27,660
I served as the acting chair.

269
00:16:28,280 --> 00:16:29,660
So you chaired that meeting

270
00:16:30,080 --> 00:16:31,540
and decided to

271
00:16:31,560 --> 00:16:32,740
replace the lead prosecutor.

272
00:16:33,480 --> 00:16:34,660
Do you think that decision

273
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:37,460
has interfered with the investigation

274
00:16:38,200 --> 00:16:39,740
or obstructed the case?

275
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:43,220
The Party Leadership Group

276
00:16:45,320 --> 00:16:46,300
holds the highest level of authority

277
00:16:47,080 --> 00:16:48,500
and has the final say
over court affairs.

278
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:50,300
Alright.

279
00:16:52,560 --> 00:16:54,780
After Zhang Wenjing was exonerated,

280
00:16:56,040 --> 00:16:57,900
did you still stand by the Wan Hai Case?

281
00:17:00,320 --> 00:17:01,460
Just because Zhang Wenjing's case
